data.title: Meet Your PCC Providers – Norton Sound Health Corporation
data.text:
Tim Lemaire, DO, MPH

Family Medicine/OB/Musculoskeletal Manipulation

Dr. Lemaire went to medical school in Portland, Oregon and completed his residency in family medicine at the Alaska Family Medicine Residency in Anchorage.

Logan Huff, DO

Family Medicine/Musculoskeletal Manipulation

Dr. Huff attended medical school in South Florida, and completed his residency in family medicine at the Alaska Family Medicine Residency in Anchorage.

Nicole Neretin, MD

Family Medicine/Acupuncture

Dr. Neretin is a certified life and health coach, and practices acupuncture and homeopathy.

Elizabeth Burgess, MD

Family Medicine

Dr. Burgess attended Wake Forest School of Medicine in North Carolina and completed her residency at West Suburban Medical Center in Chicago.

Marc Levin, MD

Family Medicine/Coordinator of Visiting Student, Resident, and Fellow Rotations Program

Dr. Levin attended Upstate Medical University in New York and completed a family medicine residency in St. Paul, MN.

Tamera Akarah, MD

Family Medicine/Obesity/Weight Management

Dr. Akarah completed her bachelor’s degree at the State University of New York and earned her medical degree at Ross University School of Medicine.

James Lavery, MD

Family Medicine

Dr. Lavery is board certified in family medicine and completed his residency training at Aultman Hospital in Canton, Ohio. He has particular interest in treating skin conditions and lesions.

Christina Penon, MD

Family Medicine

Dr. Penon

received her medical degree from Xavier University School of Medicine. She completed her residency at Texas Tech Health Sciences Center in Odessa, Texas.

Nicole La Bombarda, PA-C

Family Medicine

La Bombarda grew up in Nome and Unalakleet. She attended George Washington University and returned to the region after a few years at a community clinic in the DC metro area.

Emily Waltemyer, PA

Nome Primary Care

Waltemyer earned her bachelor’s degree in biology from the University of Maryland, and went on to complete a master’s in Physician Assistant Studies from Frostburg State University.

Mackenzie Rapp, DO, MPH

Family Medicine/Musculoskeletal Manipulation/Acupuncture

Dr. Rapp received a master’s in Medical Anthropology from the University of South Florida, and went on to earn a Masters in Public Heath from the University of Nova Southeastern in Florida. She completed her residency in family medicine in Anchorage.

Bryce Loder, MD

Family Medicine, Savoonga

Dr. Loder has been practicing family medicine for 39 years. He came to NSHC after practicing in Kansas and New Zealand.

Sarada Abraham, MD

Family Medicine/Obesity

Dr. Abraham attended medical school at the University of Rochester School of Medicine and Dentistry and completed her residency at the University of Chicago.

Jenny Maciaszek, MD, MPH

Family Medicine

Dr. Maciaszek earned her Doctorate in Medicine and master’s in public health at the University of Kansas School of Medicine. She completed her training at the Alaska Family Medicine Residency program in Anchorage.

Richelle Fisher, PA

Nome Primary Care

Fisher graduated with a master’s degree in Physician Assistant Studies from Missouri State University.

Ashley Sockpick, FNP-BC

Nome Primary Care

Sockpick grew up in Nome, and has a bachelor’s degree in Cellular & Molecular Biology. She went on to receive her master’s in nursing from Frontier Nursing University.

Coleman Straiton, DNP FNP-C

Unalakleet Provider

Straiton attended Metropolitan State college in St. Paul, MN where he earned his Doctor of Nursing Practice-Family Nurse Practitioner degree.

Cori Wasz, NP

Unalakleet Provider

Wasz attended Metropolitan State University in St. Paul, MN, where she earned her doctorate in nursing practice.

Ella Derbyshire, MD

Family Medicine

Dr. Derbyshire graduated from the St. Georges University in Grenada, West Indies in 2002. She has over 18 years of diverse experience.

Louisa Albright, PA

Unalakleet Primary Care Provider/Health Aide Trainer

Albright attended Augsburg University in Minneapolis, MN, where she earned an M.S. in Physician Assistant Studies.

Stephani Zakutansky, MD

Internal Medicine/Pediatrics

Dr. Zakutansky attended medical school at the University of Washington, and completed residency at the University of Michigan.

Kyle Pohl, MD

Internal Medicine/Pediatrics

Dr. Pohl attended medical school at Michigan State University. He completed his residency at the University of Michigan.

Angela Torres, MD

Family Medicine/OB

Dr. Torres attended medical school at Columbia University Vagelos College of Physicians and Surgeons. She has been practicing medicine for more than 20 years.

Matthew Dammeyer, MD

Family Medicine/OB

Dr. Dammeyer earned his medical degree from the University of Minnesota Medical School in Minneapolis.

Morgan Hines, MD

Family Medicine/OB

Dr. Hines graduated from the Mcgovern Medical School at the University of Texas Health Science Center in Houston in 2015. She specializes in family medicine.

Jacquelyn Serrano, MD

Family Medicine/OB

Dr. Serrano attended medical school at Stanford University. She completed her residency in Minneapolis, where she previously completed a master’s degree in Public Health.

Natalia Whitman, MD

Neurology/Acupuncture

Dr. Whitman received her medical degree from Ross University School of Medicine in 2004 and has been in practice for 16 years.

Steve Daniel, MD

Family Medicine/Diabetes

Dr. Daniel has been a board certified family physician since 1996, and has 30 years of experience.

Paul Davis, MD

Family Medicine/Gastro-Intestinal

Dr. Davis completed his medical education at ORU School of Medicine and his family medicine residency training at Lancaster General Hospital in 1986.
